adjectives.description: membranaceous (comparative more membranaceous, superlative most membranaceous)

entries.meaning: Resembling or having properties of a membrane.
examples: "Nay he confirms what his Antagonist has wrote, partly by History, and partly by Reason; affirming that himself in his own Garden found two little birds with membranaceous wings utterly devoid of Legs, their form was near to that of a Bat's."
